<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="733" type="materials_examined">
<materialsCitation pageId="25" pageNumber="733">
<paragraph blockId="25.[707,1301,603,1026]" box="[708,1301,638,671]" pageId="25" pageNumber="733">Original type locality not known. Restrict-</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[707,1301,603,1026]" box="[708,1301,677,710]" pageId="25" pageNumber="733">ed by J. L. Bonhote in 1901 to Assam, In-</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[707,1301,603,1026]" box="[708,1299,717,750]" pageId="25" pageNumber="733">dia, and further restricted by J. C. Moore</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[707,1301,603,1026]" lastBlockId="25.[96,1308,1033,3270]" pageId="25" pageNumber="733">
and G. H. H. Tate in 1965 to the Garo Hills of Assam. 
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="733" type="discussion">Reports of this squirrel often occur under the name C. flavimanus. Significant further study of the many named and the likely many as yet undocumented subspecies is required; it is possible that some may merit species level distinction. Generally, 26 subspecies are recognized, some of which were divided into four groups as below by G. B. Corbet and J. E. Hill, 1992.</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
</materialsCitation>
</subSubSection>
